WEBVTT

00:02.377 --> 00:04.003
NARRATOR:
In a land of myth...

00:04.171 --> 00:05.714
...and a time of magic...

00:05.881 --> 00:07.799
...the destiny of a great kingdom...

00:07.966 --> 00:10.886
...rests on the shoulders of a young man.

00:11.053 --> 00:14.139
His name, Merlin.

00:17.392 --> 00:19.394
[SNORING]

01:27.296 --> 01:28.797
[CLICKS]

01:49.109 --> 01:50.861
[SIZZLES]

02:23.435 --> 02:25.103
[GRUNTS]

02:29.650 --> 02:31.568
It is not worth anyone's life.

02:31.735 --> 02:33.320
Isn't it?

02:34.071 --> 02:36.073
It's cost me 20 years of mine.

02:36.239 --> 02:38.575
It is of no use.

02:38.742 --> 02:41.453
You'll never find the third part
of the triskelion.

02:41.620 --> 02:42.954
Ah, but you're wrong.

02:44.623 --> 02:46.625
| already know where that bit is.

02:46.792 --> 02:48.710
[SHOUTS]

03:44.015 --> 03:45.642
[THUNDER CRASHING]

03:49.938 --> 03:51.898
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

04:00.157 --> 04:02.117
MAN:
Hello, Gaius.

04:02.909 --> 04:04.995
Surely you remember me.

04:06.955 --> 04:08.623
Only too well.

04:10.125 --> 04:12.836
-Why are you here?
MAN: Please.

04:13.462 --> 04:16.757
| could do with drying myself by your fire.

04:24.723 --> 04:27.434
You have a nerve coming back here.

04:28.018 --> 04:30.520
You left me in a lot of trouble.

04:30.687 --> 04:34.524
Yeah. Yeah, sorry about that.

04:34.691 --> 04:39.696
What can I say?
Execution didn't really appeal to me.

04:43.116 --> 04:44.868
Don't pretend you supported Uther.

04:45.035 --> 04:47.662
Tell me why you're here.

05:02.344 --> 05:03.929
Save your eyesight, Gaius.

05:04.471 --> 05:06.473
It's the triskelion of Ashkanar.

05:06.640 --> 05:09.392
-You're sure?
-I'm certain.

05:09.559 --> 05:11.478
Let me see.

05:17.275 --> 05:19.736
This is a druid tongue.

05:19.903 --> 05:22.531
The bind runes are in threes. That's rare.

05:22.697 --> 05:24.908
MAN:
| can save you the trouble.

05:25.408 --> 05:28.537
They guide the bearer
to the tomb of Ashkanar.

05:30.914 --> 05:32.833
Yes.

05:33.792 --> 05:36.211
We both know the legend.

05:39.881 --> 05:41.550
We both know what he hid there.

05:43.593 --> 05:45.428
A dragon's egg.

05:46.263 --> 05:49.015
And you have come to steal it?

05:49.182 --> 05:50.725
| wouldn't say steal.

05:50.892 --> 05:54.563
You're forgetting one thing.
You're missing a part of the triskelion.

05:55.564 --> 05:57.065
Oh, no.

05:57.232 --> 06:00.527
- I know where that bit is.
-Where?

06:05.365 --> 06:08.952
In the vaults beneath your feet.

06:09.202 --> 06:11.329
GAIUS:
In Camelot?

06:11.496 --> 06:15.125
Where it has lain safe and secure
for the last 400 years.

06:15.625 --> 06:18.086
And you want me to help you to get it?

06:18.253 --> 06:20.463
We could bring this noble creature
back to life.

06:21.006 --> 06:22.883
[SIGHS]

06:25.677 --> 06:27.554
| want no part of your plan.

06:28.388 --> 06:30.599
MAN: You don't want to release
the last living dragon?

06:30.765 --> 06:32.559
GAIUS:
The old ways should be left to die.

06:32.726 --> 06:35.437
-Well, that's not what you taught me.
-It's what I feel now.

06:35.604 --> 06:40.191
| believe in the king that Arthur
will become and the future he will build.

06:43.028 --> 06:44.237
Think about it.

06:46.364 --> 06:48.742
I've given you my answer.

06:48.909 --> 06:52.662
Now [ think you should leave Camelot,
sooner rather than later.

06:52.829 --> 06:57.667
Arthur may not be his father,
but he is no friend of the old ways.

07:01.755 --> 07:04.466
You'll find me in the tavern
in the lower town.

07:04.633 --> 07:06.051
Take your time.

07:06.217 --> 07:07.802
Oh.

07:07.969 --> 07:12.307
Gaius, I know
| caused you trouble before...

07:12.599 --> 07:14.851
...but I'm a changed man.

07:15.352 --> 07:17.062
Believe me.

07:20.482 --> 07:22.484
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

07:28.990 --> 07:31.576
-Who was that?
-Oh, it doesn't matter.

07:31.743 --> 07:33.411
Gaius.

07:36.456 --> 07:37.916
He was a pupil.

07:38.083 --> 07:41.044
-His name is Julius Borden.
-Why won't you help him?

07:42.837 --> 07:45.924
This is our one chance
of saving the dragons.

07:46.091 --> 07:48.301
Of helping Kilgharrah preserve his kind.

07:48.468 --> 07:51.096
Borden is not a man to be trusted.

07:52.347 --> 07:54.140
You don't think the triskelion is real?

07:54.307 --> 07:57.143
-That I have no doubt.
-Then what?

07:57.310 --> 07:58.770
His motives, Merlin.

07:58.937 --> 08:01.272
Even as a young man,
he was prone to dishonesty.

08:01.439 --> 08:03.024
Who knows what path he is on now.

08:04.442 --> 08:06.152
You want the egg to remain lost forever.

08:06.319 --> 08:08.905
| don't want it to get into Borden's hands.

08:09.072 --> 08:12.033
The tomb of Ashkanar has lain untouched
for more than 400 years.

08:12.200 --> 08:14.744
It is my belief it should remain that way.

08:18.164 --> 08:19.708
Now let's get some sleep.

08:19.874 --> 08:21.960
We've a busy day ahead of us tomorrow.

08:52.032 --> 08:53.742
[BIRD SQUAWKS]

08:55.410 --> 08:59.748
| never dared dream
of such a moment, Merlin.

09:01.207 --> 09:05.587
Until now, I believed the egg
would never be found.

09:05.754 --> 09:09.382
That I would be the last of my kind.

09:09.549 --> 09:11.509
So the legend is true.

09:11.676 --> 09:15.180
This is a chance...

09:15.346 --> 09:18.266
...In a thousand, Merlin.

09:18.767 --> 09:21.686
You must retrieve the egg.

09:23.438 --> 09:27.108
- I know.
-Then what is the matter?

09:30.028 --> 09:31.696
MERLIN:
Uh--

09:33.239 --> 09:36.576
-Gaius has forbidden it.
-Merlin...

09:36.743 --> 09:38.912
...you are a Dragonlord.

09:39.079 --> 09:42.707
It is a gift passed down from your father.

09:43.208 --> 09:48.254
He gave up everything in his life to save me.

09:48.755 --> 09:51.257
What do you think he would say?

09:52.675 --> 09:58.431
The egg harbors the last of my kind.

09:59.432 --> 10:02.102
| beg you, Merlin...

10:02.268 --> 10:04.229
...in your father's name...

10:05.438 --> 10:10.026
...promise me that you will do
everything in your power...

10:10.193 --> 10:12.654
...to rescue it.

10:16.282 --> 10:18.701
You have my promise.

10:21.204 --> 10:23.540
[BELL TOLLING]

10:45.270 --> 10:46.855
Agh. No--

10:47.021 --> 10:48.398
[GRUNTS]

10:48.565 --> 10:50.900
-What do you want?
-To help you.

10:51.860 --> 10:54.737
-Who are you?
-A friend of Gaius.

10:55.947 --> 10:58.199
| heard what you told him.

10:59.159 --> 11:01.828
| want to see a dragon's egg.
| want to come with you.

11:01.995 --> 11:03.746
-Did he send you?
-No.

11:03.913 --> 11:05.623
No?

11:06.666 --> 11:09.419
-Then get out.
-Please. I know everything about dragons.

11:09.586 --> 11:10.962
-I've read everything.
-Go away.

11:11.129 --> 11:13.756
Right, but you won't
get into the vaults without me.

11:13.965 --> 11:17.886
Heh. And how's a boy like you gonna help?

11:18.511 --> 11:21.681
Because I'm the personal servant
of King Arthur.

11:54.714 --> 11:56.549
What on earth are you doing?

11:58.134 --> 12:00.261
Looking for woodworm.

12:05.683 --> 12:08.102
Before breakfast?

12:08.895 --> 12:11.648
That is when the worms are most active.

12:15.985 --> 12:17.570
Get out.

12:29.666 --> 12:31.793
These need washing.

12:32.961 --> 12:34.504
So do these.

12:37.590 --> 12:41.010
Oh, and, Merlin, before you go,
| need that belt.

12:48.351 --> 12:50.937
We need to strengthen
all our outlying defenses...

12:51.104 --> 12:53.064
...as Odin's raids only go to prove.

12:53.231 --> 12:55.650
It is the northern borders
that are particularly vulnerable.

12:55.817 --> 12:57.777
ARTHUR:
It's always been so. The reason's obvious.

12:57.944 --> 12:59.529
If you look at the terrain here--

13:03.032 --> 13:04.867
MERLIN:
Allow me to help you, sire.

13:05.034 --> 13:06.077
No. No!

13:07.412 --> 13:09.455
-Merlin.
-Your Majesty.

13:09.622 --> 13:11.165
-Merlin!
-Your Majesty!

13:11.332 --> 13:13.167
[BOTH GRUNTING]

13:13.334 --> 13:15.461
-Get off me!
-I'm trying to help you, sire.

13:17.255 --> 13:18.673
There we go.

13:18.840 --> 13:21.801
-Will there be anything else, sire?
-No!

13:32.603 --> 13:35.440
Ahem. So the terrain here--

13:47.785 --> 13:50.371
I'm beginning to like you, Merlin.

13:58.546 --> 14:00.590
This is as far as I go.

14:00.757 --> 14:02.592
Now, this key opens the last gate...

14:02.759 --> 14:05.053
...but you have to get past the guards.

14:05.803 --> 14:07.889
That won't be a problem.

14:36.167 --> 14:37.627
[COIN CLATTERS]

14:51.057 --> 14:52.767
[ALL GRUNTING]

15:02.110 --> 15:03.694
[DOOR CREAKS LOUDLY]

15:49.991 --> 15:51.492
[CHUCKLES]

16:07.633 --> 16:09.343
[SIZZLES]

16:22.982 --> 16:25.067
-Shh!
GUARD: To the right.

16:25.943 --> 16:27.695
Follow me.

16:40.917 --> 16:42.460
Thanks.

16:42.627 --> 16:44.337
Anytime.

16:47.173 --> 16:49.258
Tell me, Merlin...

16:50.426 --> 16:51.969
...would you say you're a good liar?

16:54.514 --> 16:56.265
| don't know. If I need to be.

17:02.563 --> 17:04.941
You're gonna need to be.

17:08.653 --> 17:11.489
[ROOSTER CROWS]

17:11.656 --> 17:12.906
[GASPS]

17:15.952 --> 17:17.494
[GROANS]

17:51.737 --> 17:53.447
[SIGHS]

17:58.744 --> 18:00.329
Merlin.

18:01.205 --> 18:03.958
-What are you doing?
-Shh.

18:12.675 --> 18:14.260
I'm listening for woodworm.

18:14.427 --> 18:16.470
I'm getting slightly concerned about you.

18:16.637 --> 18:19.098
[BELLS RINGING]

18:19.682 --> 18:21.976
What the hell is that?

18:24.270 --> 18:29.233
The lock hasn't been damaged,
which would suggest whoever it was had a key.

18:32.486 --> 18:34.447
Strange.

18:38.326 --> 18:41.203
Of all these treasures,
this is all they were interested in.

18:41.370 --> 18:44.832
-What was in here?
-I believe, sire, one third of a triskelion.

18:45.458 --> 18:50.212
A type of key. A key that, according to legend,
opens the ancient tomb of Ashkanar.

18:53.257 --> 18:56.886
| remember my father talk of such a tomb.
It contained a dragon's egg.

18:57.053 --> 18:59.305
-It has been said.
-You don't believe it to be true?

18:59.472 --> 19:03.351
Well, it is possible, sire. The wealth
and wisdom of Ashkanar are without equal.

19:04.226 --> 19:06.937
-Is the egg still there?
- I can't be certain.

19:07.104 --> 19:12.026
But to my knowledge, no one has disturbed
the tomb for more than 400 years.

19:12.193 --> 19:14.987
But with this triskelion,
someone could?

19:15.154 --> 19:17.698
Sire, a dragon's egg can live
for a thousand years.

19:17.865 --> 19:19.700
Even today, it could still hatch.

19:19.867 --> 19:21.619
Another dragon can
be born into this world.

19:21.786 --> 19:26.082
So all my father's work to rid the world
of these monsters would be undone?

19:26.248 --> 19:27.750
AGRAVAINE:
That must be our fear.

19:30.920 --> 19:32.004
Then we have no choice.

19:32.171 --> 19:36.092
We must hunt down this intruder,
destroy the egg.

19:38.886 --> 19:41.555
How could you be so stupid?

19:41.722 --> 19:44.892
-What were you thinking?
-I am a Dragonlord.

19:45.393 --> 19:47.812
It is my sacred duty
to protect the last of the dragons.

19:47.978 --> 19:50.940
The tomb could have remained closed
for another 400 years...

19:51.107 --> 19:53.275
...and the egg would have been
completely safe.

19:53.442 --> 19:56.487
Now Arthur's riding out,
intent on destroying it.

19:56.654 --> 19:59.782
-We have to hope that Borden gets there first.
-Oh!

19:59.949 --> 20:02.201
You trust Borden?

20:02.368 --> 20:05.579
You really think he's going to release
that dragon?

20:06.497 --> 20:09.750
Heh. I fear to think what he intends
for the poor creature.

20:09.917 --> 20:12.044
Why couldn't you leave things alone?

20:16.090 --> 20:17.508
ARTHUR:
Hurry up, Merlin!

20:27.435 --> 20:28.894
Hyah.

20:44.785 --> 20:47.204
ARTHUR:
Same hoof tracks.

20:48.122 --> 20:49.957
-Must be closing on him.
MERLIN: Look.

20:53.002 --> 20:54.754
Made camp.

20:58.257 --> 20:59.633
Hyah.

21:04.263 --> 21:07.391
-Still warm.
-Can't have more than a few hours lead on us.

21:07.558 --> 21:09.810
We need to keep moving.

21:32.583 --> 21:34.668
Deer tracks.

21:34.960 --> 21:36.712
Have we lost him?

21:36.879 --> 21:39.548
It's getting too dark to see.

21:41.801 --> 21:44.053
Have to find somewhere
to hole up for the night.

21:44.220 --> 21:45.888
But we're so close to him.

21:46.055 --> 21:49.308
Unless you can see in the dark,
Merlin, there's not much else we can do.

21:53.479 --> 21:55.356
Whoa. I'm famished.

21:57.691 --> 21:59.819
-Thank you.
-Heh.

21:59.985 --> 22:01.946
[GRUNTS]

22:02.112 --> 22:03.823
I'm hungry as a horse.

22:06.992 --> 22:10.079
That's a point, Merlin.
Have you fed them?

22:10.246 --> 22:12.540
-What?
-The horses.

22:13.707 --> 22:15.584
-Well--
-Come on. They must be starving.

22:16.544 --> 22:18.420
-But--
-On your toes.

22:29.139 --> 22:31.350
[HORSE WHINNIES]

22:33.185 --> 22:34.979
[LEAVES RUSTLE]

22:54.915 --> 22:57.751
Mm. That was lovely, Merlin.

22:57.918 --> 22:59.503
Thanks.

23:00.880 --> 23:02.631
Ugh, I loved it.

23:02.798 --> 23:04.466
LEON:
Me too.

23:07.136 --> 23:09.305
If you're gonna wash those...

23:09.471 --> 23:12.516
-...wash this too.
-Thanks.

23:12.933 --> 23:15.269
Hang on. There's still a little bit left.

23:19.023 --> 23:20.608
Oh.

23:21.609 --> 23:23.110
Mm.

23:23.986 --> 23:25.613
-Mm.
-Good, was it?

23:25.779 --> 23:27.990
Mm. A little bit salty though.

23:30.743 --> 23:32.286
Merlin.

23:33.245 --> 23:35.873
-There's another plate here.
ALL: Ha-ha-ha!

23:48.469 --> 23:50.471
GHOSTLY VOICE:
Emrys.

23:51.472 --> 23:53.057
Unh.

23:55.643 --> 23:57.728
Emrys.

24:07.321 --> 24:09.531
Emrys.

24:15.287 --> 24:16.956
Emrys.

24:17.122 --> 24:18.832
Where are you?

24:28.217 --> 24:29.760
[TWIG SNAPS]

24:31.095 --> 24:33.555
Emrys.

24:50.072 --> 24:53.784
Do not be afraid. We know your quest.

24:56.328 --> 24:59.623
-How?
-The man you seek also stole from us.

24:59.790 --> 25:03.335
He passed through these woods
not three hours before you.

25:03.502 --> 25:05.295
-Which way did he go?
-To the east.

25:05.462 --> 25:08.257
But you must be wary, Emrys.

25:08.424 --> 25:12.011
The legends tell a tale
that only the druids know.

25:13.554 --> 25:17.725
-What do they say?
-Ashkanar was a wise man.

25:18.434 --> 25:22.813
He knew one day men would come
seeking to disturb his rest.

25:23.939 --> 25:28.485
The triskelion is not just a key.

25:29.153 --> 25:30.696
It is also a trap.

25:31.363 --> 25:34.408
-What do you mean? What kind of trap?
- I do not know.

25:34.658 --> 25:36.577
But the legends are very clear.

25:36.744 --> 25:40.080
You must beware, Emrys.

25:47.379 --> 25:48.756
Emrys.

25:48.922 --> 25:51.425
There is one other thing the legends say.

25:53.510 --> 25:57.598
"Only when the way ahead
seems impossible...

25:57.765 --> 25:59.349
...will you have found it."

26:06.940 --> 26:08.942
[BIRDS SQUAWKING]

26:23.373 --> 26:24.875
He must've left in the night.

26:25.042 --> 26:27.544
-No horse tracks.
-He's covered them.

26:29.088 --> 26:31.006
We had him.

26:31.340 --> 26:32.883
We were so close.

26:33.550 --> 26:34.551
Where are you going?

26:34.718 --> 26:37.471
-We don't even know which way he went.
-He's heading east.

26:38.097 --> 26:39.973
How do you know that?

26:41.016 --> 26:42.226
Because I can sense it.

26:43.393 --> 26:45.395
Sense is not a word
| associate with you, Merlin.

26:45.562 --> 26:47.272
Hang on.

26:49.775 --> 26:51.193
He's right.

26:51.985 --> 26:53.112
He can't be.

26:53.278 --> 26:55.114
Well done, Merlin.

26:59.243 --> 27:00.786
You ever heard of the word "sorry"?

27:00.953 --> 27:03.539
No. Is that another word you made up?

27:15.801 --> 27:17.886
ARTHUR;:
It's a dead end.

27:19.388 --> 27:21.473
That's it. Let's go back.

27:22.891 --> 27:24.476
What about the cave?

27:25.978 --> 27:27.980
We're wasting our time.

27:29.022 --> 27:30.440
Arthur.

28:07.561 --> 28:10.564
Merlin, this is ridiculous.
Where's he heading?

28:11.148 --> 28:13.025
There's light ahead.

28:50.229 --> 28:53.065
GWAINE:
No wonder no one's ever found it.

29:25.931 --> 29:27.432
[SCREAMS]

29:28.267 --> 29:29.601
Take cover!

29:35.232 --> 29:37.234
-Ugh.
-You all right?

29:37.401 --> 29:38.527
Yeah.

29:41.154 --> 29:42.572
Where's he firing from?

29:47.077 --> 29:50.080
I'll draw fire. Get him to safety.

30:07.472 --> 30:08.932
Arthur.

30:44.343 --> 30:46.762
What happened? Where's he gone?

30:51.224 --> 30:53.769
MERLIN:
Perhaps he ran out of bolts.

31:04.571 --> 31:05.989
Careful!

31:09.368 --> 31:12.371
Who knows what he's left
lying in wait for us.

31:12.537 --> 31:15.165
-We can go round that.
-No.

31:15.374 --> 31:16.833
He knows we're coming.

31:17.000 --> 31:21.838
-That's a risk we have to take.
-We'll make camp, continue at dawn.

31:23.507 --> 31:25.342
[CHATTERING]

32:08.135 --> 32:10.137
Merlin, go get some more firewood.

32:10.303 --> 32:12.013
-But I was just gonna--
-Mm.

32:12.639 --> 32:15.892
Mm. Mm. Mm.

32:16.059 --> 32:18.770
This is good. Guys, you gotta try this.

32:24.651 --> 32:26.528
Mm!

32:27.028 --> 32:29.739
Mm! Mm.

32:37.581 --> 32:41.460
All right. Don't tell me. It was too salty.

32:47.716 --> 32:48.842
Typical.

32:59.436 --> 33:03.190
Well, if you think I'm doing the washing up--

33:07.486 --> 33:09.196
[ARTHUR GROANING]

33:15.744 --> 33:17.621
[GASPS]

33:21.875 --> 33:25.212
[SPEAKING INCANTATION]

34:22.561 --> 34:24.521
No!

34:37.324 --> 34:39.202
[COUGHING]

34:47.210 --> 34:49.295
[SPEAKS INCANTATION]

36:05.497 --> 36:07.624
Give it to me.

36:10.126 --> 36:12.587
It's not yours to take.

36:16.341 --> 36:18.510
You give it to me...

36:18.677 --> 36:21.429
...and I will grant you a half share, Merlin.

36:21.596 --> 36:23.306
No, it must go free.

36:23.473 --> 36:26.184
Don't be a fool.

36:26.351 --> 36:28.520
Think of the power it will bring us...

36:28.687 --> 36:32.399
...the lands we can rule over, the riches.

36:32.565 --> 36:36.736
-I'm not interested in that.
-With this dragon at our command...

36:36.903 --> 36:39.406
...we will live like kings.

36:40.281 --> 36:43.118
We will have the freedom
and power to do as we wish!

36:43.284 --> 36:44.869
Dragons cannot be used like that!

36:46.746 --> 36:50.583
They must be left unshackled,
free to roam the earth.

36:50.750 --> 36:53.086
But this is your chance, Merlin.

36:54.295 --> 36:57.799
Your chance to escape
your meaningless life...

36:57.966 --> 37:00.677
...your worthless existence.

37:00.844 --> 37:03.263
It's not my life that's pitiable. It's yours.

37:03.430 --> 37:07.642
You've wasted it for nothing.

37:15.942 --> 37:18.528
| pieced together the triskelion.

37:19.112 --> 37:21.948
| found the path that led us here.

37:22.115 --> 37:25.493
The dragon belongs to me.

37:25.702 --> 37:27.495
Now hand it over.

37:28.997 --> 37:30.623
-No.
-Aah!

37:30.790 --> 37:32.709
You're not gonna stop me, boy!

37:32.876 --> 37:35.336
Dragons are magical creatures!
They belong to no man!

37:35.503 --> 37:37.756
They are for the benefit of all!

37:39.591 --> 37:40.800
What do you know?

37:40.967 --> 37:44.304
Huh? You are but a serving boy.

37:45.138 --> 37:48.224
| am the last Dragonlord...

37:48.683 --> 37:50.351
...and I am warning you.

37:51.978 --> 37:54.063
Leave this egg alone.

37:57.942 --> 37:59.569
[GROANS]

38:18.046 --> 38:20.799
[RUMBLING]

38:42.362 --> 38:44.113
What the hell happened?

38:44.864 --> 38:48.159
The tomb was a trap. He set it off.

38:49.410 --> 38:52.372
-He never got out.
-What about the egg?

38:54.749 --> 38:58.253
- It would have perished with him.
-Are you sure? We need to be certain.

38:59.671 --> 39:02.215
Nothing's going to survive under all that.

39:19.566 --> 39:22.986
-Shame about the egg.
-Yes.

39:24.362 --> 39:25.989
You weren't able to save it?

39:27.657 --> 39:29.200
No.

39:48.887 --> 39:50.722
[LAUGHS]

39:53.099 --> 39:55.685
All the jewels, all the treasures, Gaius...

39:55.852 --> 39:57.687
...they don't compare.

40:19.834 --> 40:22.629
And it was nearly lost because of you.

40:26.049 --> 40:28.217
I'm sorry, Gaius. I was too quick to act.

40:28.384 --> 40:31.387
You have to think things through.

40:31.554 --> 40:33.222
Ashkanar did exactly that.

40:33.389 --> 40:37.518
He had the foresight to conceal this
for more than 400 years.

40:41.272 --> 40:43.858
And now it's down to you, Merlin.

40:44.901 --> 40:48.363
For you to decide
what you intend to do with it.

40:52.283 --> 40:53.868
I've thought about that.

41:00.833 --> 41:03.670
I'm going to make sure it goes back
to where it belongs.

41:37.120 --> 41:39.247
Is it still alive?

41:39.414 --> 41:42.917
It can live for more than a thousand years.

41:43.084 --> 41:44.627
[CHUCKLES]

41:45.336 --> 41:48.840
So you are no longer the last of your kind.

41:49.007 --> 41:51.759
Heh. It would seem not.

41:53.678 --> 41:54.804
When will it hatch?

41:54.971 --> 41:59.350
Young dragons were called into the world
by the Dragonlords.

41:59.976 --> 42:04.230
Only they had the power
to summon them from the egg.

42:04.397 --> 42:06.816
As the last Dragonlord...

42:07.567 --> 42:12.155
...this solemn duty falls to you, Merlin.

42:16.701 --> 42:21.456
-How do I summon it?
-You must give the dragon a name.

42:38.097 --> 42:40.892
Aithusa.

42:45.521 --> 42:46.898
[DRAGON CHATTERING]

42:52.153 --> 42:54.989
KILGHARRAH:
A white dragon...

42:55.156 --> 43:00.119
...Is indeed a rare thing, and fitting.

43:00.286 --> 43:06.167
For in the dragon tongue,
you named him after the light of the sun.

43:06.334 --> 43:10.171
No dragon birth is without meaning.

43:10.338 --> 43:13.174
Sometimes the meaning is hard to see...

43:13.341 --> 43:16.552
...but this time, I believe, it is clear.

43:17.136 --> 43:20.181
The white dragon bodes well for Albion.

43:21.682 --> 43:25.019
For you and Arthur.

43:26.020 --> 43:29.732
And for the land
that you will build together.

43:29.941 --> 43:31.984
[SHELL CRACKING]

43:33.194 --> 43:35.404
[HISSES]

43:39.575 --> 43:41.911
Merlin.

43:42.078 --> 43:43.579
AGRAVAINE:
You are untested as a king.

43:43.746 --> 43:45.706
| can't just kill a man in cold blood.

43:45.873 --> 43:48.668
You must do what you need to do
to assert your authority on this land.

43:48.835 --> 43:50.962
Do you really have the guts to kill me?

43:51.129 --> 43:53.798
You've always shown mercy in battle.
This isn't like you.

43:53.965 --> 43:56.509
The whole of Camelot will pay for this!

43:57.260 --> 43:58.594
MORGANA:
Arthur will not win...

43:58.761 --> 44:01.347
...because I have the power
to ensure that he doesn't.

44:01.514 --> 44:03.057
ARTHUR:
| made the wrong decision.

44:03.224 --> 44:06.477
Now I've brought this war
upon Camelot myself.

44:48.644 --> 44:50.646
[English - US - SDH]
